commit.message:
libeventd/protocol: Require length of parsed buffer

We hate it handy in all our relevent cases, and it is required for
libsoup’s WebSocket messages as we ask for a non-const buffer and the
NUL byte is not copied in this case.

Signed-off-by: Quentin Glidic <sardemff7+git@sardemff7.net>

verification.payload:
tree eb3279727a028586332762f2bfd6d070fa6d3e72
parent 30bde7ef964e55e924edda0fc96912a19a5dc734
author Quentin Glidic <sardemff7+git@sardemff7.net> 1672657537 +0100
committer Quentin Glidic <sardemff7+git@sardemff7.net> 1672657538 +0100

libeventd/protocol: Require length of parsed buffer

We hate it handy in all our relevent cases, and it is required for
libsoup’s WebSocket messages as we ask for a non-const buffer and the
NUL byte is not copied in this case.
